 !important; width: 593px !important; height: 26px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-5051" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><br></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680167717186" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680167717186"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 313.469px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 156.734px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 313px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="58" height="21" style="display: none; top: 46px !important; left: 115px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">Figuring out what works best for your skin can be hard. Some tips for finding suitable products are:&nbsp;</span><br></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">1. Test it out first: </span>Aim for minimalist ingredients in products, and always test out your products before applying them all over your</span><span style="background-color: var(--body_bg); color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;">&nbsp;face.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="background-color: var(--body_bg); color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">2. Be gentle to your skin</span>: That feeling when your face is extra tight, means your skin is drying out, NOT that it's extra clean. It's okay to baby your skin and go for gentle products instead of harsh ones.&nbsp;</span><br></p><p><span style="background-color: var(--body_bg); color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">3. Avoid harsh facial scrubs:</span>&nbsp;Washing your face with scrubs can damage your skin barrier. A damaged skin barrier increases the chances of infection, breakouts and dehydrated skin.&nbsp;</span><br></p><p><br></p><p>Navigating the world of skin care can be tough, but with these recommendations and tips we hope your skin care journey can be a little easier. Remember to start with a basic routine and add new products slowly.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Don't forget:</strong> it's never too late or early to start showing your skin you care.</p><p><br></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679404125859" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679404125859" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1653642484175" data-id="1653642484175"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-